<hymn_number>1930</hymn_number>
<title>Amen to the Lord</title>
<lyrics>[V1]
 You are a mighty God
 You are the faithful one forever
 You see my deepest need
 You know me altogether
 Sometimes it's true that just living
 Seems so much more, more than it should
 Than it should
 But you'll be there for me
 Loving and keeping me
 Lifting my heart and my feet to heaven

[V2]
 So I say Amen to the Lord
 Yes I say Amen to the Lord
 So I say Amen to the Lord
 My Saviour, my Fortress
 My Strength and My Hope forever

[V3]
 Upon the Mountaintop
 You show your love to me oh Lord
 There I see Vision
 Vision and meaning
 Down in the Valley
 I have questioned your love
 Your love for me, for me my Lord
 But thank you for saving me
 Thank you for loving me
 Thank you for grace and Your mercy is forever

[V4]
 So I say Amen to the Lord
 Yes I say Amen to the Lord
 So I say Amen to the Lord
 My Saviour, my Fortress
 My Strength and My Hope forever
 Amen, Amen
 Amen to the Lord</lyrics>
</song>